 Exercise  1.3 How many facts, rules, clauses, and predicates are there in the following knowledge base? What are the heads of the rules, and what are the goals they contain?

   woman(vincent).
   woman(mia).
   man(jules).
   person(X):-  man(X);  woman(X).
   loves(X,Y):-  father(X,Y).
   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  son(Z,Y).
   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  daughter(Z,Y). 

   Solution:

   Facts:
   -----
   Three facts
   woman(vincent).
   woman(mia).
   man(jules).

   Rules:
   ------
   four rules
   person(X):-  man(X);  woman(X).
   loves(X,Y):-  father(X,Y).
   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  son(Z,Y).
   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  daughter(Z,Y). 

   Clauses
   -------
   There are seven clauses
   all the given statements are clauses

   Predicates
   ----------
   there are five predicates
   woman, man, person, loves and father


   Heads and goals
   ---------------
   person(X), loves(X,Y) and father(Y,Z) are head, 

   person(X):-  man(X);  woman(X).
   for person there are two goals, either person should be a man or woman


   loves(X,Y):-  father(X,Y).
   for loves there is just one goal, to be a father for the same variable X and Y

   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  son(Z,Y).
   for father there are two goals to satisfy both man whose name is Y and have a son whose name is Z.


   father(Y,Z):-  man(Y),  daughter(Z,Y). 
   for father there are two goals to satisfy both man whose name is Y and have a daughter whose name is Z.
